Yes, there are generally some standard ways that this can be achieved for many websites and CMSs.  For example, you can reference the current page's title using a standard PHP "echo" statement, like this:

<?php

$year = date("Y"); 
echo "© {current_page_title} $year";

?>

Here is an example of PHP code that could achieve this functionality.  You would need to update the details appropriately for your website, or modify the code slightly as needed:

<?php

$year = date("Y"); 

echo "© $year My Website";

?>
